## 🧭 The core mapping (simulation → real world)

Your code:

```cpp
position += velocity * dt;
```

Real world:

* object has position
* object has velocity
* time passes
* position changes

That’s literally basic physics.

So your engine is:

* tracking objects in space ✔
* updating them over time ✔
* publishing their state ✔

That’s already a simplified **physics system**.

